Jeongyeon. I have to comment that despite this year being most trying for most, if not all people, including me, you and your members have absolutely carried me through this long and difficult year. My introduction to TWICE occurred in 2019 and I had  gradually began to learn about all of the members and the discography of TWICE. As I took  the time to learn about each of the members of the, I always found myself gravitating towards you. Before I even knew all of the membersâ€™ names, I felt this spirit within you that constantly drew me to you. One of the first qualities that I noticed about you was your warm smile. I noticed how easily you smile even if you find yourself in situations that might make you feel like you might not want to. Seeing the optimism that you have always had immediately made me feel more hopeful for the outcome of my future and the future of the world we all live in. It didnâ€™t stop there, though. During my time catching up to the history of TWICE, I have gotten the honor of seeing you perform on multiple different stages and in multiple different settings. I want to first comment on how stunning, stellar, and captivating your dancing is. Every time that I see you dance, I am reminded of what true passion and hard work is. Every movement that you make is perfect, and you leave every stage having put on a show even better than the last. Overall, you are an indescribably professional and proud performer both on and off the stage. However, perhaps your greatest charm lies within your voice. The first time that I ever heard you sing, I was completely taken aback, and even after getting acquainted to it, I am still surprised as if I am hearing it for the first time to this day. Your voice is encompassed of so much emotion, power, but delicacy and sweetness as well. It is so unique and it shines no matter what song  you sing. Your voice is so versatile and you can effortlessly sing anything and everything you want. I have been fortunate enough to get to know each of you all personally, and I see a lot of myself in you. I love how eagerly you tease your members and always have a good time with them no matter where you are. I am honored to have somebody so lovely as a role model. However, I am just one person, and I know that there are millions of people everywhere that feel just as I do. I know that your members love you and value you as a part of the group. On top of this, they cherish you as a best friend and a sister that was present and will be present for some of the most precious moments of their life. You make them laugh, cheer them up, and share their pain with them which is all that you can ask from another person. ONCE also have a lot to thank you for and praise you for. You are someone who has brought a group of different people together and teach them to love unconditionally every single day. We thank you every day for showing us so much spirit and hope. I know you have gone through a lot, both as an individual and with your group as well. I want to take this opportunity to say that I hope that this birthday shows you the same love and graciousness that you show us every day. I hope that you are surrounded only by people that love you, and that you have the most enjoyable and fulfilling birthday that you can have. We are so grateful beyond words for how much you have sacrificed to bring us endless hours of entertainment, motivational music, and unique art. How to stream for twice  1 _ log into a YouTube account  2_ to find the music video use the search bar each time  or click links from other platforms like twitter  3_ make sure to like the video after you see it all and leave a comment while you are at  it  4_  make sure not to comment 'hashtag#' or  'view ' or 'stream ' it might freeze the views  count  5_ also don't open links from the comments because that also freeze the views count  6_ Don't skip ads 7_ when streaming make the sound 60% 8_ don't change the speed of the video also known as playback speed  9_ make sure that the quality of the video is at least 480 p  10_ watch the video from start to finish without skipping any thing in between or pausing 11_  watch 2 to 3 other videos from different channels in between each stream 12_ don't open multiple tabs cause it doesn't work  13_ Not refreshing the page or clicking the reply button   just watch 2 to 3 videos each stream  14_ try not to use playlists during first 24 hours 15_ don't delete your view history  16_

2:09 Elegant Mina
Incredible achievements for Twice as the first girl group to achieve undisputed   Here are just 10 of some of their many accomplishments that were the first K-Pop girl group to achieve.   1. The first K-Pop girl group to sell 100,000 concert tickets online.   2. The first K-Pop girl group to exceed 200,000 sales in one day.   3. The first K-Pop girl group to exceed 5 million sales.   4. The first K-Pop girl group to achieve 100 PAKs.  5. The first K-Pop group to hold a Japanese dome tour, which is one of the most successful tours in the world.  6. The first K-Pop girl group to surpass 1 billion streams on GAON.  7. The first K-Pop girl group to debut at number one on both the Billboard World Albums and Singles charts.   8. The first K-Pop Girl group to receive an accredited Gaon Platinum certification.  9. The first K-Pop girl group to reach 5 million followers on Twitter.  10. The first K-Pop girl group to win a SOTY award for three years in a row

Did anyone else notice that the toys at 2:18 - 2:24 actually symbolise their previous title tracks. Eg. Dahyun holding the Bulldozer(bdz),  Chaeyoung holding ğŸ© (doughnut),  Momo holding the racket(one more time) tzuyu holding a canvas (fanfare) Sana holding that pink toy (candy pop)  Its about celebrating where they have been, where they are now, and where they are going.  I thought that little detail was really nice to see

To all the Tzuyu stans who keep claiming that she got 4 seconds in the whole MV and that they only see her once during the pre-chorus...  0:30-0:32 Solo shot 0:48-0:50 Solo shot 1:03-1:04 pop-up Tzuyu x2 1:07-1:08 Solo shot 1:21-1:22 3-shot with  Chaeng & Momo 2:23-2:24 Solo shot 2:34-2:35 2-shot with Nayeong + Solo shot 2:48-2:49 group center focus shot  The members that got the most exposure on this MV - Sana, Mina, Momo, Dahyun, and Nayeon. MiSaMo is obvious - they are Japanese, their pronunciation is excellent, and they tend to get the most lines hence the most screen time. Sana and Dahyun both have promotional contracts in Japan. Nayeon has a solo album on the charts.  Of all the members, Tzuyu is the weakest when in comes to Japanese language and pronunciation. (Yes, I speak intermediate Japanese, or at least I used to).  I'd put Chaeyoung just above her, but Chaeyoung gets away with it because of her rap parts. Weak pronunciation = less parts. That should be damn obvious to everyone, since you all know that foreign idols are expected to pronounce the Korean lyrics perfectly or else people complain.  This is the reality of OT9. You Tzuyu stans can just wait for her to release her solo, or push JYPE to release a mandarin title song. It's just annoying that so soon after Twice announces their OT9 extension of contracts, stans and akgaes are already complaining about parts distribution.  In any case, I'm OT9 - I support all of them.

26
First off...this song sounds SO MUCH BETTER on Spotify. Something about JYPE's JPN releases and their mixing, and Youtube's compression doesn't mix. Overall the song and MV is fun, but it's far from their best JPN title. Tbh, I don't find the chorus melody to be particularly catchy or attention grabbing. After getting something moody and melodically engaging as Doughnut, Celebrate feels like a step back musically. But maybe it's just me - I wasn't a huge fan of Candy Pop, but everyone else seemed to love it. I guess this song fits the theme of the moment, but I'll be looking for the b-sides to redeem this album release.   In any case, thank you Twice! OT9 Forever!!
